    "body": "Problem:  When reconfiguring a float reallocates the grid before the old\r\n          area is cleared, artifacts are left on the screen.\r\nSolution: Use the last known compositor dimensions of a grid when\r\n          clearing the area covered by the old position.\r\n\r\nFix #38143",
    "closed_at": "2026-03-11T11:38:18Z",
    "comment_data": [],
    "comment_regular_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "@glepnir's patch looked ok to me. Maybe @bfredl can comment on whether calling `win_grid_alloc()` in other places than the single callsite it had in `update_screen()` before 037ea6e7 / 66e4784f is even allowed to begin with. If those problems require different solutions maybe we shouldn't build on it.",
